SECURITY BEST PRACTICES

For robust security, use HTTPS when transmitting sensitive information and
limited cookie validation. Moreover, always validate user inputs to prevent
common attacks like cross-site scripting (XSS) and SQL Injection.

SQL injection is a severe threat to the security of web applications, enabling
attackers to execute arbitrary SQL commands. In an ASP.NET context, here are the
steps to guard against this danger.


KEY DEFENSES

 * Parameterized Queries: Eliminate SQL injection risks by using parameterized
   queries with ADO.NET.

 * Stored Procedures: Further fortify your application by defining and utilizing
   stored procedures for data access.


BEST PRACTICES

 * Least Privilege: Utilize database roles with minimal permissions to prevent
   unauthorized actions.

 * Error Handling: Employ detailed exception handling to trace, log, and notify
   about any potential injection attempts.

 * Validation & Sanitization: Scrutinize user inputs through white/blacklisting
   and server-side validation, discarding or sanitizing suspicious characters.


